Memorandum that kinge henry beinge divers tymes by Busshop Gardiner enformed against Busshoppe Cranmer, and the saide Gardiner havinge his instrucions of one Dr London a stoute and filthie prebendary of windesor, whoe theare convicted did weare a paper openlye and rodde throughe the towne with his face towardes the horse taile, and also had informacion of Mr Moyles, Mr Baker, & of sum others promooted by the said Cramner whose tales he uttred to the kinge, whoe perceivinge the malice trusted the said Cramner with thexaminacion of thes matters which he did of divers persons as by this doth appeare vide. pag. 418
