@r135@ To the fyrst Article The seyd deponent saythe that he never drewe the seyd Indyctamentes Wherby John Blanc and other were Indyctyd but folowyd the fourme of the presydent made by master Moyle To the secound Article & the fyfte & sevynthe & eighte The seyd deponent saythe that he was bedden by master moyle to putt yn the Inglysshe Wordes & folowe the presydent To the thyrde Article & to the fourthe & to the syxte The sayde deponent saythe that he never knewe of the makynge of the Indyctemient To the nynythe article The sayd deponent saythe that there was a mayde of Bevynden Indyctyd for speakynge of Woordes Agaynst the Sacrement of thalter To the xthe article The seyde deponent saythe who gave obydence he rememberythe not To the xi article The sayde deponent saythe that he knowythe nott Whether Any gave Evydence or no & for the evydence that the sayde deponent gave it were suche As were delyvered hym yn wryttynge by oone of the Justyce of peace Whome they were he rememberythe nott To the xii article The seyde deponent saythe that he dyd nott swere the Jury of ffylborowe orderly as they dyd apere in the panell but left owte one bull whyche dyd Apere for by cause master moyle thowght hym suspect notto be Indefferent to be sworne that day for the kyngs To the xiii article
The seyde deponent saythe that as concernyng such persons as shuld be Impanyllyd at the seyd Sessyons he sawe apapir of names of certeyne jurys of the seven hundreth And Aboute Assheforth to nominate of xviii persones delyvered hym by one William Master moyle Clerke on a saturday at assheforde & his master askyd me Whether they were honest men to passe for the kyngs & I sayde ye To the xiiii article The seyde deponent saythe that he was at master Twayttes the Wedynaysday next before saynte Mychaell last past & there ytt was shewyd me certeyn w in wryttyngs my master moyle of certayn woordes that shuld have ben spokyn by Bland Turnour & other & sayde there must be Indyctementes made of them and there he delivered me a fourme of Indyttmentes & they amynacious To the xvthe Article The seyde deponent saythe that the sayde master Twayttes was present with master moyle & me when the seyde mr moyle delyvered me the seyd fourme of the Indyctmentes & what communycacion we hadd, the sayd deponent remember the not other than communyng the makyng of the seyd Indyctmentes To the xvi article The seyde deponent sayth that he never hadd other communycacion then the sayd saturday with Mr moyle or one other for Impanellyng of any [guest?] that he rememberythe To the xvii article The seyde deponent saythe that he rememberythe not eny had with any man of the chayngyng of the woorde nowe past or to come or of mattere of ouer ffaythe
@r137@ To the xviii article The seyde deponent saythe that the sayde Nayler shewyd hym that my lord of Caunterbury was muche dyspleasyd with hym for woordes that he shuld speake agaynst the Jury that were Impanellyd in the Cytye of Caunterbury & askyd the me Whether I never knewe any matter yn the shere agaynst one ffrenche whiche was one of the Jury as he sayde / & I sayde that as I rememberyd I he was in the Gayle for woordes spokyn agaynst ouer soveraygn lord the kyng but what they were he knowythe nott To the xixthe article The seyde deponent saythe that he knowythe nott any ffawters or berers of any that have th tawght any erronyous oppynyons with yn the shere of kent To the xxthe Article The sayde deponent saythe that he knowythe nott any that hathe prechyd sedicyouslye other then shuche as be before Indytyd
