@r201@ Rythe worschypffull master: salutatyons gevyn: these be to declare unto yow: thatt certen honest men off the parysche off sayntt aelphegys in Canterbury whoys namys are thes: John hugden: Raffe Albrythe: Robert absolon; John Barton: Doo wytness that Thomas Batters the kynges servantt. Also William Salter the kynges bedd man dwellyng within the city off Canterbury: In the parysche off sayntt aelpheges on sayntt Georges day last past : dyd procure certen off ther noygbers to sett ther handes : other to be contentyd: to have ther namys sett unto a lettre whom they hadd dyvysyd In testymonyall ffor the honesty of ther parson: parson off sayntt aelpheges : by thatt maenes Intendyng to debare: suche honest witnesse as att thatt tyme aperyd att lambhythe be ffore my lord off Canterbury wytnessyng suche wordes : as they hard: ther parson speke a yenst the auctorite off auryculer confession: And thes ii be ffore namyd Batters a,d Salers: dyd not onely procure off ther owne parysche : butt off other parysches also suche as they knew wold bend unto them: Be syde thys: hytt ys here reportyd by honest men: thatt batters: thatt same day: sayde unto John hugden with hige crake: thatt the parson off saynt aelpheges : was troblyd : onley by the maenes off gardner and Schether: butt he dowtyd nott butt thatt gardner and also Schether schuld qwayle: Worschypffull master: thes and suche lyke wordes may geve grett cause to bold men: In ther evyll doynges: unlesse that yowr masterschyppe ffynd remedy to cause thes bold spekers to temper ther tongues : God preserve yow: Canterbury William Gardner prieste
